<br>
I agree that there's not many things out there for high end players in LDoN.  It was fun the first few days, after that it's all the same.  Only thing I've bought through my points were the 3 spells that use to open chests/boxes.  The other new spells that they've introduced for druids aren't remotely useful at all.  I've seen some items from hard missions, I don't know if I'd ever use any of them personally if without those extra slots for augmentation. (Most of them have more them just type 1 slots).<br>
<br>
For high end players, maybe the raid would be fun, the raid I did, trash mobs hit up to 1084 and it takes awhile to single pull.  <br>
<br>
As for LoY, I actually like it a lot.  It makes level 30-50 possible without doing OT/IceClad/DL.  There are places for solo players and grouping.  It makes life easier on a new server since some of the mobs do drop decent items for a nontwink char.  Other than the xp, share bank slots, and maps are nice too.  I know some people who has good sense of direction and probably never need a map to go from one place to the other, but for me, map option is like god send.<br>
<br>
Overall, I still like LoY and LDoN at this point.  One thing I really appreciate LDoN is once again, we can tell the nitwits from the people who have common sense in a group. <p><!--EZCODE FONT START--><span style="color:maroon;font-family:comic sans;"><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=376166" target="top"><!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>Raiya Lemmingwarden</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--></a><!--EZCODE LINK END--></span><!--EZCODE FONT END--><br>
